  "notes": "Primary data parsed directly from the RFEG club page's embedded per-hole tables (club id 169, recorridos still named \"HACIENDA ALAMO\"). All checks pass: pars sum to 72 (36/36), stroke indexes are a permutation of 1-18, and every tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its published total (Negras 3318+3406=6724; Blancas 3157+3218=6375; Amarillas 2967+3027=5994; Rojas 2723+2811=5534; Naranjas 2195+2154=4349). Cross-checks: Hole19's hole-by-hole card matches RFEG's Blancas tee exactly (par, SI, all 18 distances); Golfshake's totals in yards convert exactly to RFEG meters for all five tees (Black 7353y, White 6972y, Yellow 6555y, Red 6052y, Orange 4756y). Stroke index shown is the men's Negras/Blancas/Amarillas allocation per RFEG. Discrepancies/caveats: (1) Rojas and Naranjas (both genders) use a different RFEG SI allocation: 5,7,11,15,17,1,9,13,3 (front) / 14,4,16,12,8,18,6,2,10 (back); Amarillas (F) uses that same alternate allocation. (2) Some third-party sites label the 6724 m tee \"Blancas\" and shift other names down one color (e.g. golfinspain, and Hole19 calls the 6375 m tee \"Amarillas\"); the RFEG/official card naming used here is Negras/Blancas/Amarillas/Rojas/Naranjas. (3) Naranjas is orange, mapped to \"gray\" since orange is not an allowed color value. (4) RFEG also lists A+A, B+B and \"Provisional H10\" 18-hole variants (nine played twice), excluded as they are not the main routing; the 6 short/academy holes are unrated and have no RFEG card."
